
The '''speno-maxillary fossa''' is a small triangular space situated at the angle of the junction of the spheno-maxillary and pterygo-maxillary  fissures, and placed beneath the apex of the orbit. It is formed above by the under surface of the body of the [[Sphenoid bone|sphenoid]] and by the [[orbital process]] of the [[palate bone]].

